            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am very glad to hear both from you &amp; <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> that he proceeds with such
                    spirit. I wish he had some book that w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> instruct him
                    in perspective for I w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> fain have him make all the
                    drawings he can of places that may never again be visited by the curious
                    traveller. you mention <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0100">something</title>
                    </bibl> that <sic>
                        <persName ref="pe0231">y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> printer</persName> have done</sic> ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    <placeName ref="pl0737">S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Kilda</placeName>: pray
                    what is it. I am impatient to see his sheet about <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0101">the Genealogies</title>
                    </bibl>. Be so go<gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="2"/> as to forward the inclosed
                    which will oblige</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.
                    1773</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p>Best wishes of the season attend you.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
